The paper discusses recent progress on unsupervised and semi-supervised methods for learning with small data, which is a common problem in many machine learning applications. The paper covers a wide range of topics, including autoencoders, generative adversarial networks, domain adaptation, and transformation equivariance and invariance, which are all relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. Based on the content of the paper, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
